                         bertrpc.js

This is a BERT-RPC <http://bert-rpc.org> server built on
node.js  <http://nodejs.org/>,  the V8 based evented IO
framework.

The  bert.js  library  was  taken  from  Rusty Klophaus's
BERT-JS  project: <http://github.com/rklophaus/BERT-JS>.

INSTALL

node.js must be installed and available on your PATH
before continuing.

USAGE

Once you have node installed, grab a clone of the
node-bertrpc git repo

    $ git clone git://github.com/rtomayko/node-bertrpc
    $ cd node-bertrpc
    $ node examples/mathrpc.js
      <--  exposing: math

Now use a BERTRPC client to connect:

    $ irb -rubygems -rbertrpc
    >> remote = BERTRPC::Service('localhost', 7000)
    >> remote.call.math.sum([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
    => 15

You should also see something like the following output from
the server:

    -->  connect
    -->  [45] {call,math,sum,1,2,3,4,5}
    <--  [13] {reply, 15}
    -->  eof
    <--  close
